---
title: GR00T Actions To Joints To DDS
---
flowchart LR

  %% This diagram focuses on the joint mapping and actuation boundary.
  %% Labels intentionally use spaces only (no \n) for Mermaid compatibility.

  subgraph Bridge[Closed loop bridge process]
    Cam[ZMQ camera frames] --> Obs[Build observation dict]
    State[ROS state topic /G1Env/env_state_act] --> Obs

    Obs --> Client[GR00T PolicyClient RPC]
    Client --> Actions[GR00T action outputs dict]

    Actions --> Map[Map action groups to target joint vectors]
    Map --> Goal[Pack msgpack goal dict]
    Goal --> Pub[Publish ROS goal topic /ControlPolicy/upper_body_pose]

    NoteTime[target_time is required by InterpolationPolicy] --> Goal
  end

  subgraph WBC[Whole body control loop process]
    Sub[Subscribe /ControlPolicy/upper_body_pose] --> Interp[Upper body InterpolationPolicy]
    Interp --> WBCPolicy[G1DecoupledWholeBodyPolicy]
    WBCPolicy --> QDes[Desired joint positions and hand commands]
  end

  Pub --> Sub

  subgraph Actuation[Actual actuation channels]
    LowCmd[DDS rt/lowcmd motor commands]
    DexL[DDS rt/dex3/left/cmd hand commands]
    DexR[DDS rt/dex3/right/cmd hand commands]
  end

  QDes --> LowCmd
  QDes --> DexL
  QDes --> DexR

  subgraph Mapping[Action keys map to joint groups]
    ActionsKeys[Example action keys left_arm right_arm waist left_hand right_hand]
    Groups[RobotModel joint groups and indices]
    ActionsKeys --> Groups
    Groups --> Upper[target_upper_body_pose vector]
  end

  Actions --> ActionsKeys
  Groups --> Map

